{"DEN":[{"def":"A narrow glen; a ravine; a dell.","pos":""}],"DENARCOTIZE":[{"def":"To deprive of narcotine; as, to denarcotize opium.","pos":""}],"DENARIUS":[{"def":"A Roman silver coin of the value of about fourteen cents; the \"penny\" of the New Testament; -- so called from being worth originally ten of the pieces called as.","pos":""}],"DENARY":[{"def":"Containing ten; tenfold; proceeding by tens; as, the denary, or decimal, scale.","pos":""}],"DENATIONALIZATION":[{"def":"The or process of denationalizing.","pos":""}],"DENATIONALIZE":[{"def":"To divest or deprive of national character or rights.","pos":""}],"DENATURALIZE":[{"def":"To render unnatural; to alienate from nature.","pos":""},{"def":"To renounce the natural rights and duties of; to deprive of citizenship; to denationalize.","pos":""}],"DENATURE":[{"def":"To deprive of its natural qualities; change the nature of.","pos":""}],"DENAY":[{"def":"That with great rage he stoutly doth denay.","pos":""}],"DENDRACHATE":[{"def":"Arborescent or dendritic agate.","pos":""}],"DENDRIFORM":[{"def":"Resembling in structure a tree or shrub.","pos":""}],"DENDRITE":[{"def":"A stone or mineral on or in which are branching figures resembling shrubs or trees, produced by a foreign mineral, usually an oxide of manganese, as in the moss agate; also, a crystallized mineral having an arborescent form, e.","pos":""},{"def":"Pertaining to a dendrite, or to arborescent crystallization; having a form resembling a shrub or tree; arborescent.","pos":""}],"DENDROCOELA":[{"def":"A division of the Turbellaria in which the digestive cavity gives off lateral branches, which are often divided into smaller branchlets.","pos":""},{"def":"Resembling a shrub or tree in form; treelike.","pos":""}],"DENDROLITE":[{"def":"A petrified or fossil shrub, plant, or part of a plant.","pos":""}],"DENDROLOGIST":[{"def":"One versed in the natural history of trees.","pos":""}],"DENDROLOGOUS":[{"def":"Relating to dendrology.","pos":""}],"DENDROLOGY":[{"def":"A discourse or treatise on trees; the natural history of trees.","pos":""}],"DENDROMETER":[{"def":"An instrument to measure the height and diameter of trees.","pos":""}],"DENGUE":[{"def":"A specific epidemic disease attended with high fever, cutaneous eruption, and severe pains in the head and limbs, resembling those of rheumatism; -- called also breakbone fever.","pos":""}],"DENIABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being, or liable to be, denied.","pos":""}],"DENIAL":[{"def":"The act of gainsaying, refusing, or disowning; negation; -- the contrary of affirmation.","pos":""},{"def":"A refusal to admit the truth of a statement, charge, imputation, etc.","pos":""}],"DENIER":[{"def":"One who denies; as, a denier of a fact, or of the faith, or of Christ.","pos":""}],"DENIGRATE":[{"def":"To blacken thoroughly; to make very black.","pos":""}],"DENIGRATION":[{"def":"The act of making black.","pos":""}],"DENIGRATOR":[{"def":"One who, or that which, blackens.","pos":""}],"DENIM":[{"def":"A coarse cotton drilling used for overalls, etc.","pos":""}],"DENITRATION":[{"def":"A disengaging, or removal, of nitric acid.","pos":""}],"DENITRIFICATION":[{"def":"The act or process of freeing from nitrogen; also, the condition resulting from the removal of nitrogen.","pos":""}],"DENITRIFY":[{"def":"To deprive of, or free from, nitrogen.","pos":""}],"DENIZATION":[{"def":"The act of making one a denizen or adopted citizen; naturalization.","pos":""}],"DENIZE":[{"def":"To make a denizen; to confer the rights of citizenship upon; to naturalize.","pos":""}],"DENIZEN":[{"def":"A dweller; an inhabitant.","pos":""},{"def":"One who is admitted by favor to all or a part of the rights of citizenship, where he did not possess them by birth; an adopted or naturalized citizen.","pos":""}],"DENIZENATION":[{"def":"Denization; denizening.","pos":""}],"DENIZENIZE":[{"def":"To constitute (one) a denizen; to denizen.","pos":""}],"DENIZENSHIP":[{"def":"State of being a denizen.","pos":""}],"DENMARK SATIN":[{"def":"See under Satin.","pos":""}],"DENNET":[{"def":"A light, open, two-wheeled carriage for one horse; a kind of gig.","pos":""}],"DENOMINABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being denominated or named.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATE":[{"def":"To give a name to; to characterize by an epithet; to entitle; to name; to designate.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATION":[{"def":"The act of naming or designating.","pos":""},{"def":"That by which anything is denominated or styled; an epithet; a name, designation, or title; especially, a general name indicating a class of like individuals; a category; as, the denomination of units, or of thousands, or of fourths, or of shillings, or of tons.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIONAL":[{"def":"Pertaining to a denomination, especially to a sect or society.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIONALISM":[{"def":"A denominational or class spirit or policy; devotion to the interests of a sect or denomination.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIONALIST":[{"def":"One imbued with a denominational spirit.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIONALLY":[{"def":"In a denominational manner; by denomination or sect.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIVE":[{"def":"Connotative; as, a denominative name.","pos":""},{"def":"Derived from a substantive or an adjective; as, a denominative verb.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATIVELY":[{"def":"By denomination.","pos":""}],"DENOMINATOR":[{"def":"That number placed below the line in vulgar fractions which shows into how many parts the integer or unit is divided.","pos":""},{"def":"That part of any expression under a fractional form which is situated below the horizontal line signifying division.","pos":""}],"DENOTABLE":[{"def":"Capable of being denoted or marked.","pos":""}],"DENOTATE":[{"def":"To mark off; to denote.","pos":""}],"DENOTATION":[{"def":"The marking off or separation of anything.","pos":""}],"DENOTATIVE":[{"def":"Having power to denote; designating or marking off.","pos":""}],"DENOTE":[{"def":"To mark out plainly; to signify by a visible sign; to serve as the sign or name of; to indicate; to point out; as, the hands of the clock denote the hour.","pos":""},{"def":"To be the sign of; to betoken; to signify; to mean.","pos":""}],"DENOTEMENT":[{"def":"Sign; indication.","pos":""}],"DENOTIVE":[{"def":"Serving to denote.","pos":""}],"DENOUEMENT":[{"def":"The unraveling or discovery of a plot; the catastrophe, especially of a drama or a romance.","pos":""},{"def":"The solution of a mystery; issue; outcome.","pos":""}],"DENOUNCE":[{"def":"To make known in a solemn or official manner; to declare; to proclaim (especially an evil).","pos":""},{"def":"To proclaim in a threatening manner; to threaten by some outward sign or expression.","pos":""}],"DENOUNCEMENT":[{"def":"Solemn, official, or menacing announcement; denunciation.","pos":""}],"DENOUNCER":[{"def":"One who denounces, or declares, as a menace.","pos":""}],"DENSE":[{"def":"Having the constituent parts massed or crowded together; close; compact; thick; containing much matter in a small space; heavy; opaque; as, a dense crowd; a dense forest; a dense fog.","pos":""},{"def":"Stupid; gross; crass; as, dense ignorance.","pos":""}],"DENSELY":[{"def":"In a dense, compact manner.","pos":""}],"DENSENESS":[{"def":"The quality of being dense; density.","pos":""}],"DENSIMETER":[{"def":"An instrument for ascertaining the specific gravity or density of a substance.","pos":""}],"DENSITY":[{"def":"The ratio of mass, or quantity of matter, to bulk or volume, esp.","pos":""}],"DENT":[{"def":"A stroke; a blow.","pos":""},{"def":"A slight depression, or small notch or hollow, made by a blow or by pressure; an indentation.","pos":""}],"DENTAL":[{"def":"Formed by the aid of the teeth; -- said of certain articulations and the letters representing them; as, d t are dental letters.","pos":""}],"DENTALISM":[{"def":"The quality of being formed by the aid of the teeth.","pos":""}],"DENTALIUM":[{"def":"A genus of marine mollusks belonging to the Scaphopoda, having a tubular conical shell.","pos":""}],"DENTARY":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or bearing, teeth.","pos":""},{"def":"The distal bone of the lower jaw in many animals, which may or may not bear teeth.","pos":""}],"DENTATE-CILIATE":[{"def":"Having the margin dentate and also ciliate or fringed with hairs.","pos":""}],"DENTATE-SINUATE":[{"def":"Having a form intermediate between dentate and sinuate.","pos":""}],"DENTATELY":[{"def":"In a dentate or toothed manner; as, dentately ciliated, etc.","pos":""}],"DENTATION":[{"def":"Formation of teeth; toothed form.","pos":""}],"DENTED":[{"def":"Indented; impressed with little hollows.","pos":""}],"DENTELLE":[{"def":"An ornamental tooling like lace.","pos":""}],"DENTEX":[{"def":"An edible European marine fish (Sparus dentex, or Dentex vulgaris) of the family Percidæ.","pos":""}],"DENTICETE":[{"def":"The division of Cetacea in which the teeth are developed, including the sperm whale, dolphins, etc.","pos":""}],"DENTICLE":[{"def":"A small tooth or projecting point.","pos":""},{"def":"Furnished with denticles; notched into little toothlike projections; as, a denticulate leaf of calyx.","pos":""}],"DENTICULATION":[{"def":"A diminutive tooth; a denticle.","pos":""}],"DENTIFEROUS":[{"def":"Bearing teeth; dentigerous.","pos":""}],"DENTIFORM":[{"def":"Having the form of a tooth or of teeth; tooth-shaped.","pos":""}],"DENTIFRICE":[{"def":"A powder or other substance to be used in cleaning the teeth; tooth powder.","pos":""}],"DENTIGEROUS":[{"def":"Bearing teeth or toothlike structures.","pos":""}],"DENTIL":[{"def":"A small square block or projection in cornices, a number of which are ranged in an ornamental band; -- used particularly in the Ionic, Corinthian, and Composite orders.","pos":""}],"DENTILABIAL":[{"def":"Formed by the teeth and the lips, or representing a sound so formed.","pos":""},{"def":"A dentilabial sound or letter.","pos":""}],"DENTILAVE":[{"def":"A wash for cleaning the teeth.","pos":""}],"DENTILE":[{"def":"A small tooth, like that of a saw.","pos":""}],"DENTILINGUAL":[{"def":"Produced by applying the tongue to the teeth or to the gums; or representing a sound so formed.","pos":""},{"def":"A dentilingual sound or letter.","pos":""}],"DENTILOQUIST":[{"def":"One who speaks through the teeth, that is, with the teeth closed.","pos":""}],"DENTILOQUY":[{"def":"The habit or practice of speaking through the teeth, or with them closed.","pos":""}],"DENTINAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to dentine.","pos":""}],"DENTINE":[{"def":"The dense calcified substance of which teeth are largely composed.","pos":""}],"DENTIPHONE":[{"def":"An instrument which, placed against the teeth, conveys sound to the auditory nerve; an audiphone.","pos":""}],"DENTIROSTER":[{"def":"A dentirostral bird.","pos":""}],"DENTIROSTRAL":[{"def":"Having a toothed bill; -- applied to a group of passerine birds, having the bill notched, and feeding chiefly on insects, as the shrikes and vireos.","pos":""}],"DENTISCALP":[{"def":"An instrument for scraping the teeth.","pos":""}],"DENTIST":[{"def":"One whose business it is to clean, extract, or repair natural teeth, and to make and insert artificial ones; a dental surgeon.","pos":""},{"def":"Pertaining to dentistry or to dentists.","pos":""}],"DENTISTRY":[{"def":"The art or profession of a dentist; dental surgery.","pos":""}],"DENTITION":[{"def":"The system of teeth peculiar to an animal.","pos":""}],"DENTIZE":[{"def":"To breed or cut new teeth.","pos":""}],"DENTOID":[{"def":"Shaped like a tooth; tooth-shaped.","pos":""}],"DENTURE":[{"def":"An artificial tooth, block, or set of teeth.","pos":""}],"DENUDATION":[{"def":"The laying bare of rocks by the washing away of the overlying earth, etc.","pos":""}],"DENUDE":[{"def":"To divest of all covering; to make bare or naked; to strip; to divest; as, to denude one of clothing, or lands.","pos":""}],"DENUNCIATE":[{"def":"To denounce; to condemn publicly or solemnly.","pos":""}],"DENUNCIATION":[{"def":"Proclamation; announcement; a publishing.","pos":""},{"def":"The act of denouncing; public menace or accusation; the act of inveighing against, stigmatizing, or publicly arraigning; arraignment.","pos":""}],"DENUNCIATIVE":[{"def":"Same as Denunciatory.","pos":""}],"DENUNCIATOR":[{"def":"One who denounces, publishes, or proclaims, especially intended or coming evil; one who threatens or accuses.","pos":""}],"DENUNCIATORY":[{"def":"Characterized by or containing a denunciation; minatory; accusing; threatening; as, severe and denunciatory language.","pos":""}],"DENUTRITION":[{"def":"The opposition of nutrition; the failure of nutrition causing the breaking down of tissue.","pos":""}],"DENY":[{"def":"To declare not to be true; to gainsay; to contradict; -- opposed to affirm, allow, or admit.","pos":""},{"def":"To refuse (to do something or to accept something); to reject; to decline; to renounce.","pos":""}],"DENYINGLY":[{"def":"In the manner of one denies a request.","pos":""}]}